
[1]zest

   ZEST, n.

   1. A piece of orange or lemon peel, used to give flavor to liquor; or
   the fine thin oil that spurts out of it when squeezed; also, the woody
   thick skin quartering the kernel of a walnut.

   2. Relish; something that gives a pleasant taste; or the taste itself.

                                 ZEST, v.t.

   1. To give a relish or flavor to; to highten taste or relish.

   2. To cut the peel of an orange or lemon from top to bottom into thin
   slips; or to squeeze the peel over the surface of any thing.
